<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://gohugo.io/" version="0.85.0">Hugo</generator><title type="html">version on ilo</title><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/version/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="HTML"/><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/version/index.xml" rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="RSS"/><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/version/atom.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" title="Atom"/><updated>2021-07-12T04:56:11+00:00</updated><id>https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/version/</id><entry><title type="html">Version</title><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/usage/version/?utm_source=atom_feed" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><id>https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/usage/version/</id><published>2020-04-13T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2020-04-13T00:00:00+00:00</updated><content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In order to see the version of <code>ilo</code> itself, run <code>ilo --version</code> or <code>ilo -V</code>. Its output looks something like this:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre class="chroma"><code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">$ ilo --version
ilo: 0.0.0-SNAPSHOT
JVM: 11.0.8 <span class="o">(</span>Oracle Corporation Substrate VM GraalVM 20.2.0 Java 11<span class="o">)</span>
OS:  Linux 5.7.17-200.fc32.x86_64 amd64
</code></pre></div>]]></content><category scheme="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/categories/usage" term="usage" label="usage"/><category scheme="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/version" term="version" label="version"/></entry></feed>